---

I completely missed the boat on this one, but apparently, ten months ago, [Chyrp came back](http://chyrp.net/2010/12/06/chyrp-is-back/).

Provided the project persists and progresses, I might consider taking another look at the platform that I had once loved. In the meantime, I'll stick with Habari - which I have grown accustomed to. I know that Chyrp is a very young product, but it's sudden termination was simply [too much to bear](http://ootput.wordpress.com/2010/06/02/official-chyrp-development-halted/) - I honestly can't get my hopes up again.

<!--more-->

Truth be told, I'm actually very pleased to hear that the product was restarted - it would have been a shame to have let such a promising piece of software go to waste. Even Chyrps website's design was delicious:
![7180191615_fd16650d0b](http://ootput.files.wordpress.com/2011/10/7180191615_fd16650d0b.jpg)

I wish the team the best of luck with all of [their endeavours](http://chyrp.net/2011/08/12/open-source-awards-2011-nominations-the-release-of-chyrp-211/).